    "Body": " Ace Hotel New York is seeking a Director of Finance who will be responsible for overseeing all financial aspects of the property and enforcing company standards to ensure long term success. As well as provide guidance to senior management team to maximize profits and manage and develop the accounting team. The position reports directly to the Managing Director and the Corporate Controller. Job Requirements: - Four year degree in accounting or finance - Four or more years of related hospitality experience or training; or equivalent combination of education and experience. - Must be able to prepare financial statements including cash flows and forecasts and analyze the results - Should be comfortable with reviewing regulatory and legal documents as they pertain to the role - Must be able to communicate clearly and effectively - Must be proficient in Excel and accounting software - Must be proficient in English (written and verbal) Job Functions (include but are not limited to the following): - Protect the assets of the company by establishing, monitoring and enforcing policies and procedures - Ensure all standards are met with a focus on the brand and culture - Lead and motivate the accounting team to its full potential - Support the Managing Director to create the best operations possible. Advise and guide Department Heads on hotel matters and help analyze and execute difficult decisions - Effectively represent the hotel and brand to capital partners/owners, manage their expectations, and maintain relationships - Produce timely and accurate financials reports. Effectively communicate the results to the Managing Director, Corporate Office, and other Department Heads - Oversee budgets and expenses - Work with department heads to develop and implement best practices and other operating procedures - Project operating results and advise management of any significant changes or risks - Communicate company goals to team members - Ensure compliance with all company and regulatory requirements - Oversee legal, contractual, and insurance matters of the company - Work closely with Human Resources to ensure compliance with labor laws - Manage audits as they are required - Oversee all legal and insurance matters of the company (contract with the suppliers, lessee, etc.) - Think creatively and seek new business and/or expense saving opportunities - Recognize and address weaknesses in the operations including internal controls and staff skills - Provide financial expertise (including detailed analysis, as appropriate) to assist in the overall control and planning of the business, and work with the Department Managers to support, guide and educate them in financial matters to ensure maximum profitability - Execute any other ad hoc assignments that may be assigned ", 
